cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a novel method for image classification using deep convolutional decision jungle (CDJ) and its learning algorithm. The method involves using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and decision trees to selectively respond to class labels and learn features automatically. This makes it highly relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of entropy loss and stochastic gradient descent (SGD) optimization, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on image classification benchmarks, which is relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
